      }
    ],
    "role": "article",
    "roleHeading": "Article",
    "title": "Storing Data a Pass Makes with Custom Sample Positions for a Subsequent Pass"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A render or compute pass usually stores its target’s depth data in a compressed format. Any subsequent pass has to use the correct sample positions to decompress the data before reading it. You can store depth data in a representation that uses arbitrary sample positions (see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/positioning-samples-programmatically",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ").",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "You can sample depth positions programmatically only on devices that support programmable sample positions (see ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLDevice/areProgrammableSamplePositionsSupported",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ").",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Important",
          "style": "important",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When your app uses custom sampling positions, inform Metal by setting the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderPassColorAttachmentDescriptor",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderPassDepthAttachmentDescriptor",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " instance’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderPassAttachmentDescriptor/storeActionOptions",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " property to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLStoreActionOptions/customSamplePositions",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". This setting tells Metal that any subsequent pass that reads the attachment may not know the sample positions the current pass uses to generate the data. Examples of a pass that can use custom sample positions include the following:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "A fragment shader that uses unique, programmable sample positions",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "A blit pass that copies MSAA depth data to another resource",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "In this scenario, Metal may decompress the depth render target and store the uncompressed data.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "Improve the performance of a pass if its programmable sample positions are the same for the next pass by setting the descriptor’s ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderPassAttachmentDescriptor/storeAction",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " property to ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLStoreAction/store",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " and clearing the ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLStoreActionOptions/customSamplePositions",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " option from the ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderPassAttachmentDescriptor/storeActionOptions",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " property.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Tip",
          "style": "tip",
          "type": "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
